<Layout title="Positioning" description="How to describe and pitch Needle.">
  <h1>Positioning & pitch</h1>

  <h2>The core idea</h2>
  <blockquote>
    Every other app helps you <strong>plan</strong>. Needle helps you <strong>let go of one task and
    start the next</strong> — the exact moment focus is lost.
  </blockquote>
  <p>
    Needle is <strong>not a to-do app</strong> and <strong>not a timer</strong>. It is a
    <strong>transition coach</strong>: it catches you at the moment of the switch, helps you clear
    your head, and points you at the next thing. It rotates how it interrupts you so your brain never
    learns to ignore it.
  </p>

  <h2>One-liner</h2>
  <blockquote>"Needle helps you switch from one task to the next without carrying the last one in your head."</blockquote>

  <h2>15-second pitch</h2>
  <blockquote>
    You know that moment when one meeting ends and the next one starts, but your head is still stuck
    in the last one? Needle catches you right there. It stops you for ten seconds, makes you dump
    what's on your mind, and you walk into the next thing clear. And it keeps changing <em>how</em> it
    interrupts you, so your brain never learns to ignore it.
  </blockquote>

  <h2>How to pitch in person</h2>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Start with the pain</strong> — "you know that moment when…"</li>
    <li><strong>One person, one sentence</strong> — not a feature list</li>
    <li><strong>Say what it's NOT</strong> — "not another to-do app"</li>
    <li><strong>End with a question</strong> — "Does that happen to you?"</li>
    <li>
      <strong>Why me (back pocket)</strong> — ADHD coaching insight: the brain habituates; novelty is
      the antidote
    </li>
  </ol>

  <h2>White space</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Category</th><th>Examples</th><th>What it misses</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Timers</td><td>Llama Life, Tiimo</td><td>You set it; doesn't act <em>at</em> the transition</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Body doubling</td><td>Focusmate, Centered</td><td>Scheduled; not about the switch itself</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Daily planners</td><td>Sunsama, Akiflow</td><td>One ritual/day, not every transition</td></tr>
      <tr><td>OS focus</td><td>Apple Focus</td><td>Silences interruptions — opposite mechanism</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>The obvious objection</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>"Why won't I just set a timer?"</strong> — A timer becomes wallpaper within a week. The
    rotating kit is built so that never happens. That's the moat.
  </p>

